        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 6 at 8:20AM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 820 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles west of Rocksprings, moving northeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Rocksprings and Devil's Sinkhole State Natural Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for
south central Texas.</instruction>
